      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Of course, if you prefer FOSS, OpenJDK is the platform of choice, but (as usual with these corporate troglodytes) Oracle imposes certain hooks in their version that prevents porting of some apps (and most java webstart apps) between java platforms. This defeats the main objective of Java, namely portability, which is why they are shooting themselves in the foot by practicing vendor lock-in... Long Live the Python! Long Live!"
