    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1362676021,
    "creation_date" : 1362676021,
    "answer_id" : 15277376,
    "question_id" : 10165693,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you start eclipse using oracle java, then eclipse might fail in finding native libraries like SWT or SVN libraries. The SWT-JNI libraries are located in /usr/lib/jni/ and the SVN-JNI libraries are located in /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/jni/.</p>\n\n<p>Instead of starting eclipse with the command</p>\n\n<pre><code>eclipse\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>you can use the command</p>\n\n<pre><code>env LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/lib/jni/:/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/jni/:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH eclipse\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>to pass the environment variable LD_LIBRARY_PATH to eclipse. Eclipse will find the native libraries and will run properly.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1751004,
      "reputation" : 71,
      "user_id" : 1600091,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/19f7f79d2b69299fb9193031455fd93a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Martin B.",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1600091/martin-b"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1364151750,
    "creation_date" : 1364151750,
    "answer_id" : 15602672,
    "question_id" : 10165693,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Please make sure that your home partition is mounted with executable permissions. That is the default, but if you happen to mount it without exec option, you will get this error.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2542861,
      "reputation" : 115,
      "user_id" : 2208295,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/IN2aY.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "leroneb",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2208295/leroneb"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1365088871,
    "last_edit_date" : 1365088871,
    "creation_date" : 1365087552,
    "answer_id" : 15814825,
    "question_id" : 10165693,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I agree with Scott, what he listed worked. However just running it from any directory did not work. I had to cd to the /home/<strong>*</strong>/.swt/lib/linux/x86_64/ 0 files</p>\n\n<p>directory first and then run the link command: </p>\n\n<p>For 32 bit:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ln -s /usr/lib/jni/libswt-* ~/.swt/lib/linux/x86/\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And on Ubuntu 12.04 64 bit:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ln -s /usr/lib/jni/libswt-* ~/.swt/lib/linux/x86_64/\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1361566,
