      "comment_id" : 115358244,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@padman Copying files that were installed by package management (APT in this case) is <i>not</i> a good idea. The copied files <i>won&#39;t</i> be under package management and you risk getting all kinds of other errors later on when the files under package management get upgraded. Instead, find a way to point your Eclipse to the correct location of these libraries (see dzlatkov &#39;s answer above)."
    } ],
