    "creation_date" : 1396376396,
    "answer_id" : 22793793,
    "question_id" : 10165693,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case, I was missing the <code>/usr/lib/jni</code> directory entirely. Fixed by</p>\n\n<pre><code>sudo apt-get install libswt-gtk-3-jni libswt-gtk-3-java\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>No need to symlink afterwards. Eclipse started normally.</p>\n"
